-- Database: MYChamp

-- DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS "MYChamp";

CREATE DATABASE "MYChamp"
    WITH
    OWNER = postgres
    ENCODING = 'UTF8'
    LC_COLLATE = 'English_United States.1252'
    LC_CTYPE = 'English_United States.1252'
    LOCALE_PROVIDER = 'libc'
    TABLESPACE = pg_default
    CONNECTION LIMIT = -1
    IS_TEMPLATE = False;

-- Table: public.VisitUsInformation

-- DROP TABLE IF EXISTS public."VisitUsInformation";

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public."VisitUsInformation"
(
    "Id" integer NOT NULL GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY ( INCREMENT 1 START 1 MINVALUE 1 MAXVALUE 2147483647 CACHE 1 ),
    "Icon" text COLLATE pg_catalog."default" NOT NULL,
    "Name" character varying(100) COLLATE pg_catalog."default" NOT NULL,
    "Link" character varying(250) COLLATE pg_catalog."default" NOT NULL,
    "Active" smallint NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
    "ImageType" character varying(10) COLLATE pg_catalog."default",
    CONSTRAINT visitusinformation_pkey PRIMARY KEY ("Id")
)

TABLESPACE pg_default;

ALTER TABLE IF EXISTS public."VisitUsInformation"
    OWNER to postgres;

/* register database */

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS users (
    Id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    Name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    Email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    Password VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    Address VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
);

/* user data storing after login */

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS sessions (
    Id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    UserId VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    SessionId VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    IPAddress VARCHAR(100),
    LoginTime TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    IsActive BOOLEAN NOT NULL,
    Status INT NOT NULL,
    ForcefullyLogout BOOLEAN NOT NULL,
    ForcefullyLogoutBy VARCHAR(100),
    UniqueId VARCHAR(255),
    LogoutType VARCHAR(50)
);
